verbose_text: Inhibiting prostaglandin E2 (PGE2), which is considered as a promoter of the pathogenesis of endometriosis, can suppress migration and invasion of human immortalized endometriotic epithelial and stromal cells by increasing the expression of TIMP1, TIMP2, TIMP3, and TIMP4 proteins [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: expression of TIMP1, TIMP2, TIMP3, and TIMP4
